text: Mubisa hydroelectric power station Mubisa power station is a small hydroelectric power station in Ernen, Switzerland. It is the first power station commissioned by Gommerkraftwerke AG It was commissioned in 1964 and has two 13MW pelton turbinesGKW Ernen ==References== Category:Hydroelectric power stations in Switzerland Category:Energy infrastructure completed in 1964
title: Mubisa power station
